&lt;p&gt;P-1487&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you excel at driving operations at scale? Do you like to and lead process improvements to ensure their success? Are you passionate about Release Management and building relationships across organizations? If you are, then join us at Databricks!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building a team of passionate Technical Program Managers to create and guide Release Management processes across our Engineering organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will implement and improve release processes for code through development, test, and production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will work with our engineering and product team members to ensure Databricks solutions are engineered for reliability, scalability, and security - all while keeping operations top of mind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll guide the direction of cross-cloud programs, set engineering goals and launch programs at scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be front and center of organizing controls, governance and standards across our infrastructure to achieve product stability and at least four nines of uptime&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ll be reporting to a Technical Program Leader while working across multiple time-zones, seeing around corners to identify blockers, and ensuring needs are balanced against technical requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of technical program/project/relationship management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in a related field (EE, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading cross-functional teams to complete projects with multiple dependencies and constraints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining releases, identifying risks, managing cost, coordinating scope, identifying dependencies, scheduling and deploying new products and features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience creating and cascading processes through an organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using Jira&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
