&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Supply Chain AI Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to lead the strategy, development, and scaling of AI-driven products across end-to-end supply chain processes. This role sits at the intersection of business, data science, and technology, translating supply chain problems into high-impact AI solutions that improve forecast accuracy, service levels, inventory performance, and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the product vision and roadmap for AI capabilities across areas such as Advanced Supply Chain Planning ( demand sensing, supply planning, inventory optimization), order management, Procurement and decision automation, partnering closely with Supply Chain operations teams , X-functional business technology teams, Data Science, and Finance teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a hybrid position requiring 3 days per week in our Bangalore office and 2 days working remotely. Relocation assistance will not be provided for this role. This position requires working hours in the IST time zone.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Strategy &amp;amp; Vision&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and own the AI product vision, roadmap, and success metrics for supply chain use cases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify high-value opportunities where AI/ML can drive measurable business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize features based on ROI, feasibility, data readiness, and user impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Use Case Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate supply chain challenges into clear AI problem statements and product requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with internal teams to design, validate, and scale ML models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide experimentation, pilots, and MVPs to move from conceptual ideas to production-ready AI products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the POC for AI products across E2E Supply Chain Space&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross functional teams on data pipelines, integrations, and MLOps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption by working closely with business users, change management, and training teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end product lifecycle from ideation through deployment and continuous improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define user stories, acceptance criteria, and backlog prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure solutions are scalable, explainable, and aligned with governance and compliance standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Measurement &amp;amp; Continuous Improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define KPIs such as forecast accuracy, inventory turns, service levels, cycle time, and automation rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor model performance and business impact post-deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine models and features based on feedback and data insights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Champion and embed Samsara&#39;s cultural principles (Focus on Customer Success, Build for the Long Term, Adopt a Growth Mindset, Be Inclusive, Win as a Team) as the company scales globally and across new offices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements for the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in Product Management, Supply Chain, or Digital Transformation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of end-to-end supply chain processes (Design to Release, Forecast-to-Plan/Build, Order-to-Cash, Procure-to-Pay)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience delivering AI/ML or advanced analytics products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate complex business problems into technical requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to collaborate effectively with both technical and non-technical global stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to overlap with NA working hours for collaborative tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with agile project management methodologies and tools along with strong documentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and decision-making abilities, with keen attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An Ideal Candidate Also Has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with ERP systems (NetSuite, Oracle, SAP) or Advanced Planning Systems (E2open, Kinaxis, Blue Yonder, SAP IBP, o9).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Large Language Models and core ML concepts (forecasting, optimization, classification, anomaly detection,etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data platforms (Databricks, Azure, AWS, GCP)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA or Master’s degree in Supply Chain, Analytics, or related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
