&lt;p&gt;Scale’s Robotics business unit is currently seeing historic levels of growth. As a &lt;strong&gt;Technical Program Manager (TPM) for Robotics Data&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be the connective tissue across our most complex technical operations, driving initiatives that secure $XXM+ in new revenue.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This isn&#39;t a &quot;sit back and watch&quot; project management role. You will work with multiple project leads across a vast portfolio of robotics data projects, ensuring technical milestones are met, dependencies are de-risked, and stakeholders are aligned. You should be prepared to wear many hats - from debugging hardware rigs to architecting data pipelines - and be excited about intense, impactful work that leads to accelerated career progression.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Multi-Project Outcomes:&lt;/strong&gt; Serve as the primary driver for a portfolio of robotics projects, tracking milestones, deliverables, and dependencies to ensure on-time delivery for the world’s leading AI researchers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bridge the Technical-Operational Gap:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the central liaison between AI researchers, hardware engineers, and global operational teams to translate high-level research goals into executable data collection and annotation workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect Scalable Pipelines:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with engineering to design and optimize end-to-end data ingestion pipelines, ensuring they can handle the high-fidelity sensor data (video, logs, teleop) required for Vision-Language-Action (VLA) models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage Hardware &amp;amp; Logistics:&lt;/strong&gt; Coordinate the setup, maintenance, and scaling of physical robotic platforms and data collection rigs across multiple sites.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Enforce Data Quality &amp;amp; Governance:&lt;/strong&gt; Define KPIs and Quality Assurance (QA) metrics to ensure datasets are high-fidelity, labeled correctly, and compliant with rigorous privacy and safety standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Standardize for Scale:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop and refine Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) that allow us to scale collection and annotation efforts across global, distributed teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communicate with Precision:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide regular, data-driven progress updates to Scale’s executive team, utilizing SQL and dashboards to monitor performance and guide strategic pivots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ideally, you’d have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong Technical Foundation:&lt;/strong&gt; A degree in Engineering, Computer Science, or a related field, combined with a deep understanding of the AI/ML data lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2-3+ Years of TPM Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven track record of managing complex, cross-functional technical programs, ideally in robotics, hardware, or large-scale data operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-on Problem Solving Skills: &lt;/strong&gt;A proactive approach to overcoming technical and logistical roadblocks in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Grit:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience &quot;in the weeds&quot; of operational challenges - you don’t just identify bottlenecks; you build the solution to clear them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entrepreneurial Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable with ambiguity and excited about building infrastructure from scratch in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SQL Proficiency:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to pull your own data and build your own tracking dashboards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience interacting with distributed teams or collection sites across different time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robotics Domain Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiarity with robotic hardware, sensor calibration, or the nuances of collecting data for Physical AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI/CV Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiarity with Computer Vision or Large Language Model (LLM) training requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
