&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since launching Cloudflare Workers in 2017, we&#39;ve evolved from an edge compute platform into a comprehensive developer platform. Now, we&#39;re expanding into AI infrastructure, specifically focusing on making Cloudflare an excellent platform for building and deploying AI agents.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role offers the opportunity to shape how developers build AI-powered applications. You&#39;ll own the strategy and execution for AI agents and Model Context Protocol (MCP) integration on Cloudflare&#39;s platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AI landscape is evolving toward more autonomous systems – agents that can use tools, access data, and perform tasks. With our global network, edge compute capabilities, and developer tools, Cloudflare is well-positioned to support these workloads. You&#39;ll help define our approach to this emerging market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the vision, strategy, and roadmap for our AI Agent platform and MCP implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with early-adopter customers and developers to shape the MVP and define the user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead cross-functional projects from protocol design through to global launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with engineering to build secure, reliable, and performant infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with the AI community and partners to drive an open, interoperable agent ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Marketing, Sales, and Developer Relations to drive product adoption and growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ruthlessly prioritize features and investments in a rapidly evolving market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Skills &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an entrepreneurial and technical product leader who is obsessed with the future of software and has a passion for building world-class developer experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep passion for the AI landscape, including LLMs, multi-agent systems, and interoperability protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional product management experience, ideally on a technical, developer-facing platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of shipping products from ideation to launch.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to articulate a bold vision that inspires and motivates your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical grasp of developer platforms, AI applications, and network protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer-obsessed, with direct experience working with early adopters to find product-market fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with developer tools and profound empathy for the challenges developers face.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some programming experience (e.g., Python, Javascript, Go) is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation may be adjusted depending on work location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;For Bay Area based hires: Estimated annual salary of $202,000 - $246,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;For New York City, Washington, Washington D.C. and California (excluding Bay Area) based hires: Estimated annual salary of $192,000 - $234,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-root=&quot;1&quot;&gt;For Colorado based hires: Estimated annual salary of $170,000 - $208,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
